WEBVTT

1
00:00:44.845 --> 00:00:47.891
All right, sweet pea, it's
time for you to go to bed.

2
00:00:47.915 --> 00:00:51.395
Mommy, would you ask
Daddy to come tuck me in?

3
00:00:51.419 --> 00:00:53.897
No, he's at work
tonight at the fire station.

4
00:00:53.921 --> 00:00:56.099
But he'll be home
tomorrow night.

5
00:00:56.123 --> 00:00:58.435
Mommy, I want to marry Daddy.

6
00:00:58.459 --> 00:01:00.103
Ha-ha-ha. You do?

7
00:01:00.127 --> 00:01:01.905
Catherine, you
can't marry Daddy.

8
00:01:01.929 --> 00:01:03.306
He's my husband.

9
00:01:03.330 --> 00:01:05.509
Well, when you're
done being married,

10
00:01:05.533 --> 00:01:06.809
can I have him?

11
00:01:06.833 --> 00:01:08.912
Ha-ha. We'll never be done.

12
00:01:08.936 --> 00:01:11.381
You'll have to marry
somebody else.

13
00:01:11.405 --> 00:01:14.217
Can I wear a white
dress and white gloves?

14
00:01:14.241 --> 00:01:16.086
Sure, if you want to.

15
00:01:16.110 --> 00:01:19.122
Will we live happily after ever?

16
00:01:19.146 --> 00:01:23.660
Mm-hm. If you marry somebody
who really, really loves you.

17
00:01:23.684 --> 00:01:25.462
Like Daddy?

18
00:01:25.486 --> 00:01:28.265
Yes, like Daddy.

19
00:02:31.918 --> 00:02:33.263
Terrell, man, my bad out there.

20
00:02:33.287 --> 00:02:36.600
This ain't no game. You
playing with people lives.

21
00:02:36.624 --> 00:02:38.290
Come on, man.

22
00:02:41.094 --> 00:02:42.872
Eric, he's got a right
to be upset with you.

23
00:02:42.896 --> 00:02:45.142
You left him in a dangerous
spot and tried to be a hero.

24
00:02:45.166 --> 00:02:47.977
But captain, I thought I
heard someone calling for help.

25
00:02:48.001 --> 00:02:50.913
It was coming from
outside the building.

26
00:02:50.937 --> 00:02:52.415
It was dark, I couldn't see.

27
00:02:52.439 --> 00:02:54.251
That's why you stay
with your partner.

28
00:02:54.275 --> 00:02:55.852
He had no choice but to assume

29
00:02:55.876 --> 00:02:59.789
that something happened to
you and you needed his help.

30
00:02:59.813 --> 00:03:03.215
You never leave your
partner, especially in a fire.

31
00:03:05.286 --> 00:03:07.497
You give him some time
and then give him an apology.

32
00:03:07.521 --> 00:03:09.166
And make it sincere.

33
00:03:09.190 --> 00:03:10.622
Yes, sir.

34
00:03:20.301 --> 00:03:21.311
Hey, Tasha.

35
00:03:21.335 --> 00:03:22.479
Oh, hey, Cat.

36
00:03:22.503 --> 00:03:24.347
Just saw you on
TV. Looking good.

37
00:03:24.371 --> 00:03:27.284
Oh, I missed it. I was giving
a tour of the new cancer wing.

38
00:03:27.308 --> 00:03:28.418
Hey, has Robin left yet?

39
00:03:28.442 --> 00:03:29.419
No, she's here.

40
00:03:29.443 --> 00:03:31.188
Robin, Cat's here.

41
00:03:31.212 --> 00:03:32.689
Hey. How are you?

42
00:03:32.713 --> 00:03:34.023
I'm good. How are you?

43
00:03:34.047 --> 00:03:36.025
Good. Hey, are we
still on for tomorrow?

44
00:03:36.049 --> 00:03:38.895
Yeah, 4:00. You still want
those scented candles, right?

45
00:03:38.919 --> 00:03:40.330
Oh, absolutely. Bring 'em on.

46
00:03:40.354 --> 00:03:41.631
I wanna try them all. Good.

47
00:03:41.655 --> 00:03:43.600
Hey, I'm going to see
my parents this weekend.

48
00:03:43.624 --> 00:03:45.101
I thought they
might like some too.

49
00:03:45.125 --> 00:03:46.969
Oh, how are they?

50
00:03:46.993 --> 00:03:49.806
Do you know it's been a
year since Mom's stroke?

51
00:03:49.830 --> 00:03:51.974
Well, I've been trying to
get her a new hospital bed

52
00:03:51.998 --> 00:03:55.645
and wheelchair, but their
insurance doesn't cover it.

53
00:03:55.669 --> 00:03:58.081
I don't know. It's so
frustrating for my dad.

54
00:03:58.105 --> 00:03:59.282
He wants to help her too,

55
00:03:59.306 --> 00:04:01.117
but, I mean, he
can't afford it either.

56
00:04:01.141 --> 00:04:02.151
I am so sorry.

57
00:04:02.175 --> 00:04:03.353
Yeah, it's all right.

58
00:04:03.377 --> 00:04:04.688
Anyway, well, I need to run,

59
00:04:04.712 --> 00:04:06.155
but I'll see you
tomorrow, right?

60
00:04:06.179 --> 00:04:07.257
Right. I'll see you.

61
00:04:07.281 --> 00:04:08.991
Okay, bye. Bye.

62
00:04:09.015 --> 00:04:10.026
Oh.

63
00:04:10.050 --> 00:04:11.094
Hey, Catherine.

64
00:04:11.118 --> 00:04:12.729
I'm so sorry, Dr. Keller.

65
00:04:12.753 --> 00:04:14.598
Call me Gavin, please.

66
00:04:14.622 --> 00:04:17.367
Gavin, sorry for
almost running you over.

67
00:04:17.391 --> 00:04:19.102
Anytime. It's good to see you.

68
00:04:19.126 --> 00:04:20.403
You too. Take care.

69
00:04:23.797 --> 00:04:25.942
Sweet girl.

70
00:04:25.966 --> 00:04:27.344
Tasha, will you
file this for me?

71
00:04:27.368 --> 00:04:29.534
Sure, doctor.

72
00:04:32.773 --> 00:04:34.050
If I didn't know any better,

73
00:04:34.074 --> 00:04:37.787
I'd say the doctor
has a thing for Cat.

74
00:04:37.811 --> 00:04:40.111
Mm-hm. Mm-hm.

75
00:04:49.890 --> 00:04:51.501
Hi, sweetheart. Hey, Daddy.

76
00:04:51.525 --> 00:04:52.502
How are you?

77
00:04:52.526 --> 00:04:54.203
Oh, great. Good to see you.

78
00:04:54.227 --> 00:04:55.572
You too.

79
00:04:55.596 --> 00:04:57.140
Hey, Mama.

80
00:04:57.164 --> 00:04:59.809
How are you, huh?

81
00:04:59.833 --> 00:05:01.711
She's doing great today.

82
00:05:01.735 --> 00:05:03.647
Could I get you
something to drink, dear?

83
00:05:03.671 --> 00:05:05.282
Uh, do you have any sweet tea?

84
00:05:05.306 --> 00:05:06.583
With lemon?

85
00:05:06.607 --> 00:05:09.452
Ha. You know me.

86
00:05:12.313 --> 00:05:15.146
Oh, Mama, I wish we could talk.

87
00:05:16.483 --> 00:05:19.596
It's been so long since
I heard your voice.

88
00:05:23.223 --> 00:05:24.989
I miss you.

89
00:05:51.352 --> 00:05:53.552
You have breakfast already?
- Yes.

90
00:05:55.422 --> 00:05:56.499
What'd you eat?

91
00:05:56.523 --> 00:05:59.023
I had the last
bagel and a yogurt.

92
00:06:06.500 --> 00:06:08.978
Are you planning on
making a grocery trip soon?

93
00:06:09.002 --> 00:06:11.614
Caleb, you work 24 hours
and then you're off for 48.

94
00:06:11.638 --> 00:06:13.115
You've got more
time to go than I do.

95
00:06:13.139 --> 00:06:15.017
Hey, I just asked
you a simple question.

96
00:06:15.041 --> 00:06:16.786
You don't need to
get smart with me.

97
00:06:16.810 --> 00:06:18.388
You could save
me some breakfast.

98
00:06:18.412 --> 00:06:20.189
I never know when
you're coming or going.

99
00:06:20.213 --> 00:06:21.524
You don't tell me these things.

100
00:06:21.548 --> 00:06:23.393
Catherine, what is your problem?

101
00:06:23.417 --> 00:06:25.662
Did I offend you by walking
in the door this morning?

102
00:06:25.686 --> 00:06:27.564
No. You just can't expect
me to work every day

103
00:06:27.588 --> 00:06:28.898
and still get the groceries

104
00:06:28.922 --> 00:06:31.067
while you sit home looking
at trash on the Internet

105
00:06:31.091 --> 00:06:32.736
and dreaming about
getting your boat.

106
00:06:32.760 --> 00:06:34.136
You chose to take this job.

107
00:06:34.160 --> 00:06:35.905
And no one said you
had to work full-time.

108
00:06:35.929 --> 00:06:37.507
We need the income.

109
00:06:37.531 --> 00:06:39.809
Especially since you tuck
away a third of your salary

110
00:06:39.833 --> 00:06:41.644
saving for a boat we don't need.

111
00:06:41.668 --> 00:06:43.713
You've got $24,000 in savings

112
00:06:43.737 --> 00:06:46.082
while we have things in
our house that need fixing.

113
00:06:46.106 --> 00:06:47.149
Like what?

114
00:06:47.173 --> 00:06:48.918
The back door
needs to be painted,

115
00:06:48.942 --> 00:06:50.553
the yard needs
better landscaping.

116
00:06:50.577 --> 00:06:53.122
And I keep telling you I wanna
put more shelves in the closet.

117
00:06:53.146 --> 00:06:55.992
Those are called preferences,
Catherine. Those are not needs.

118
00:06:56.016 --> 00:06:58.227
There's a difference. If you
wanna spend your money

119
00:06:58.251 --> 00:06:59.529
on that stuff, go ahead. Fine.

120
00:06:59.553 --> 00:07:01.330
But I've been saving
for my boat for years.

121
00:07:01.354 --> 00:07:02.699
You're not taking that from me.

122
00:07:02.723 --> 00:07:05.268
This is so pointless. I
don't have time for this.

123
00:07:05.292 --> 00:07:07.036
Yeah, shut the door
on your way out.

124
00:07:29.316 --> 00:07:32.028
<i>♪ I've been saving her
For weeks, you know ♪</i>

125
00:07:32.052 --> 00:07:33.132
<i>♪ It's time to let her go ♪</i>

126
00:07:42.429 --> 00:07:44.062
It ain't working, Michael.

127
00:07:45.332 --> 00:07:47.310
How is it that I get
respect everywhere I go

128
00:07:47.334 --> 00:07:49.646
except in my own house?

129
00:07:49.670 --> 00:07:53.382
I've been there, and
it's a hard place to be.

130
00:07:54.575 --> 00:07:56.953
What'd you do about it?

131
00:07:56.977 --> 00:07:59.823
I realized that it wasn't my
marriage that was broken.

132
00:07:59.847 --> 00:08:02.367
I just didn't know
how to make it work.

133
00:08:03.316 --> 00:08:05.383
What does that mean?

134
00:08:06.987 --> 00:08:08.230
That treadmill's not broken,

135
00:08:08.254 --> 00:08:09.699
but if you don't
know how to run it,

136
00:08:09.723 --> 00:08:11.055
it ain't gonna work for you.

137
00:08:13.093 --> 00:08:14.904
You saying I need counseling?

138
00:08:14.928 --> 00:08:17.006
Well, I think everybody
needs counseling.

139
00:08:17.030 --> 00:08:19.241
Hey, look, man, I
am not about to go

140
00:08:19.265 --> 00:08:21.110
talk to somebody
I don't even know

141
00:08:21.134 --> 00:08:23.546
about something that's
none of their business.

142
00:08:23.570 --> 00:08:26.716
All right. Catherine
does need to respect you.

143
00:08:26.740 --> 00:08:28.751
But just remember,
a woman's like a rose.

144
00:08:28.775 --> 00:08:31.654
If you treat her
right, she'll bloom.

145
00:08:31.678 --> 00:08:33.845
If you don't, she'll wilt.

146
00:08:36.116 --> 00:08:37.527
Where'd you get that?

147
00:08:37.551 --> 00:08:39.618
Counseling.

148
00:08:58.104 --> 00:08:59.983
Great.

149
00:09:00.007 --> 00:09:02.251
What are you doing?

150
00:09:02.275 --> 00:09:04.554
I see you left me no pizza.

151
00:09:04.578 --> 00:09:06.990
Caleb, I just lit that candle.
I like the way it smells.

152
00:09:07.014 --> 00:09:09.291
Well, I don't. Did you
leave me any dinner at all?

153
00:09:09.315 --> 00:09:11.127
I assumed you were
eating with Michael.

154
00:09:11.151 --> 00:09:13.930
Does it not occur to you
that there are two people

155
00:09:13.954 --> 00:09:16.198
living in this house, and
both of them need to eat?

156
00:09:16.222 --> 00:09:18.668
You know what, Caleb? If you
would communicate with me,

157
00:09:18.692 --> 00:09:20.391
maybe I could have
something for you.

158
00:09:21.929 --> 00:09:24.641
Why do you have to make
everything so difficult?

159
00:09:24.665 --> 00:09:26.308
Oh, I'm making
everything difficult?

160
00:09:26.332 --> 00:09:28.511
Seems to me like I'm
carrying the weight around here

161
00:09:28.535 --> 00:09:30.179
while you're off
doing your own thing.

162
00:09:30.203 --> 00:09:32.181
Excuse me? I'm the one out there

163
00:09:32.205 --> 00:09:34.918
working to pay this mortgage,
and I pay for both of the cars.

164
00:09:34.942 --> 00:09:36.118
Yeah, and that's all you do.

165
00:09:36.142 --> 00:09:38.154
I pay all of our
bills with my salary.

166
00:09:38.178 --> 00:09:40.089
Which you agreed
to do. That's fair.

167
00:09:40.113 --> 00:09:42.258
Do you not like this house?
Do you not like your car?

168
00:09:42.282 --> 00:09:44.928
Oh, Caleb, who takes
care of this house?

169
00:09:44.952 --> 00:09:46.763
Me. Who washes all the clothes?

170
00:09:46.787 --> 00:09:48.397
Me. Who gets all the groceries?

171
00:09:48.421 --> 00:09:51.367
Me. Not to mention I'm helping
my parents every weekend.

172
00:09:51.391 --> 00:09:53.169
You know, I've got
all this pressure on me,

173
00:09:53.193 --> 00:09:55.638
and the only thing you ever
do for anybody is for yourself.

174
00:09:55.662 --> 00:09:57.406
Let me tell you
something, you don't know

175
00:09:57.430 --> 00:09:59.241
the first thing about pressure.

176
00:09:59.265 --> 00:10:02.879
All right? You think I-I put
out house fires for myself?

177
00:10:02.903 --> 00:10:05.915
Or...? Or rush to car
wrecks at 2 a.m. for myself?

178
00:10:05.939 --> 00:10:09.619
Or pull a child's body
out of a lake for myself?

179
00:10:09.643 --> 00:10:12.121
You have no idea
what I go through.

180
00:10:12.145 --> 00:10:14.591
Oh, yeah, but what do you do
around here other than watch TV

181
00:10:14.615 --> 00:10:16.893
and waste time on the
Internet? You know what?

182
00:10:16.917 --> 00:10:19.562
If looking at that trash is
how you get fulfilled, that's fine,

183
00:10:19.586 --> 00:10:21.464
but I will not compete with it.

184
00:10:21.488 --> 00:10:23.722
Well, I sure don't
get it from you.

185
00:10:24.825 --> 00:10:26.869
And you won't.
Because you care more

186
00:10:26.893 --> 00:10:28.905
about saving for
your stupid boat

187
00:10:28.929 --> 00:10:32.108
and pleasing yourself
than you ever did about me.

188
00:10:32.132 --> 00:10:35.377
Shut up! I'm sick of you!

189
00:10:35.401 --> 00:10:38.314
You disrespectful,
ungrateful, selfish woman!

190
00:10:38.338 --> 00:10:39.315
I'm not selfish.

191
00:10:39.339 --> 00:10:40.917
How dare you say that to me?

192
00:10:40.941 --> 00:10:44.721
You constantly nag me and
you drain the life out of me!

193
00:10:44.745 --> 00:10:46.823
I'm tired of it!

194
00:10:46.847 --> 00:10:48.992
If you can't give me
the respect I deserve...

195
00:10:49.016 --> 00:10:50.493
Look at me!

196
00:10:50.517 --> 00:10:53.051
Then what's the
point of this marriage?

197
00:11:00.093 --> 00:11:02.905
I want out.

198
00:11:02.929 --> 00:11:05.030
I just want out.

199
00:11:05.932 --> 00:11:07.576
If you want out,

200
00:11:07.600 --> 00:11:09.646
that's fine with me!

201
00:11:45.205 --> 00:11:46.771
Mr. Rudolph.

202
00:11:48.041 --> 00:11:49.140
Caleb.

203
00:12:32.619 --> 00:12:33.696
That's it.

204
00:12:33.720 --> 00:12:34.731
All right.

205
00:12:34.755 --> 00:12:36.565
Think we got it.
We're good to go.

206
00:12:36.589 --> 00:12:38.034
I think I got this.

207
00:12:38.058 --> 00:12:39.702
You think you know the truck?

208
00:12:39.726 --> 00:12:41.303
Yeah. All right.

209
00:12:41.327 --> 00:12:42.705
I'll tell you what.

210
00:12:42.729 --> 00:12:45.474
We're gonna go inside
and get something to drink.

211
00:12:45.498 --> 00:12:47.676
You bring me a hose stretcher.

212
00:12:47.700 --> 00:12:49.134
All right.

213
00:12:50.203 --> 00:12:51.547
That's mean, man.

214
00:12:51.571 --> 00:12:53.816
Nah, it's good for him.

215
00:12:53.840 --> 00:12:55.284
Mother's gifts. Okay.

216
00:12:55.308 --> 00:12:56.318
And... You know what?

217
00:12:56.342 --> 00:12:57.353
I forgot to tell you.

218
00:12:57.377 --> 00:12:58.821
I got Friday off
and I'll be there.

219
00:12:58.845 --> 00:12:59.956
Good.

220
00:12:59.980 --> 00:13:01.557
You know I ain't
gonna let my son down.

221
00:13:01.581 --> 00:13:02.859
I know you won't.

222
00:13:02.883 --> 00:13:04.927
Hey, we still got that
hot date tomorrow, right?

223
00:13:04.951 --> 00:13:06.362
Oh, so now it's a hot date?

224
00:13:06.386 --> 00:13:08.798
Mm. Life's too short
to have any other kind.

225
00:13:08.822 --> 00:13:10.466
You're right.

226
00:13:10.490 --> 00:13:11.634
I love you, baby.

227
00:13:11.658 --> 00:13:13.803
Oh, I love you too.

228
00:13:13.827 --> 00:13:15.604
And I will see
you in the morning.

229
00:13:15.628 --> 00:13:16.973
All right. Back home.

230
00:13:16.997 --> 00:13:18.897
All right, see you later.

231
00:13:23.069 --> 00:13:25.469
Eric, what are you doing?

232
00:13:26.807 --> 00:13:29.185
Um, Wayne told me to
grab a hose stretcher.

233
00:13:29.209 --> 00:13:30.319
A hose stretcher?

234
00:13:30.343 --> 00:13:32.554
Yes, sir.

235
00:13:32.578 --> 00:13:35.579
Eric, you are the
hose stretcher.

236
00:13:39.352 --> 00:13:40.919
Man.

237
00:13:45.125 --> 00:13:46.936
Honey, I agree with
you. You gotta get out.

238
00:13:46.960 --> 00:13:48.304
He don't deserve you.

239
00:13:48.328 --> 00:13:50.506
You can say that again. A
real man's gotta be a hero

240
00:13:50.530 --> 00:13:52.675
to his wife before he
can be to anybody else,

241
00:13:52.699 --> 00:13:53.943
or he ain't a real man.

242
00:13:53.967 --> 00:13:55.611
Catherine, do you
need a place to stay?

243
00:13:55.635 --> 00:13:57.914
I can't imagine living in the
same house with that man.

244
00:13:57.938 --> 00:14:00.316
No, I decided lat night that
I am not the one leaving.

245
00:14:00.340 --> 00:14:01.483
He's the problem, not me.

246
00:14:01.507 --> 00:14:03.452
That's right, girl.
Stand your ground.

247
00:14:03.476 --> 00:14:04.887
Make him respect you.

248
00:14:04.911 --> 00:14:07.290
If there's one thing
a man understands...

249
00:14:07.314 --> 00:14:09.025
It's respect. That's the issue.

250
00:14:09.049 --> 00:14:10.893
That's the reason
our marriage is failing.

251
00:14:10.917 --> 00:14:13.329
She shows me no respect at all.

252
00:14:13.353 --> 00:14:15.031
And the saddest
part about it is...

253
00:14:15.055 --> 00:14:17.133
He doesn't have a clue.

254
00:14:17.157 --> 00:14:19.535
He thinks our marriage has
been fine for the most part.

