570
00:30:20.519 --> 00:30:23.031
<i>♪ I'm just a geek, remember?
Janey, never call me again ♪</i>

571
00:30:24.924 --> 00:30:25.901
Oh, come on!

572
00:30:25.925 --> 00:30:27.903
Whoo! That ain't funny.

573
00:30:27.927 --> 00:30:30.105
This ain't no show.

574
00:30:30.129 --> 00:30:31.572
This is me time.

575
00:30:32.998 --> 00:30:34.309
Terrell!

576
00:30:34.333 --> 00:30:35.610
Wayne.

577
00:30:39.805 --> 00:30:40.949
Forty days?

578
00:30:40.973 --> 00:30:43.351
Does Catherine know?

579
00:30:43.375 --> 00:30:44.752
I'm not gonna tell her.

580
00:30:44.776 --> 00:30:48.023
If she wants to go ahead
and file, that's up to her.

581
00:30:48.047 --> 00:30:50.792
Divorce is a hard thing, man.

582
00:30:50.816 --> 00:30:52.527
Well, if it brings peace...

583
00:30:52.551 --> 00:30:55.931
But Caleb, you want
the right kind of peace.

584
00:30:55.955 --> 00:30:57.187
What do you mean by that?

585
00:30:58.490 --> 00:31:00.668
You know what that ring
on your finger means?

586
00:31:00.692 --> 00:31:02.470
Means I'm married. Yeah.

587
00:31:02.494 --> 00:31:04.672
Well, it also means you
made a lifelong covenant,

588
00:31:04.696 --> 00:31:07.575
you putting on that ring
while saying your vows.

589
00:31:07.599 --> 00:31:09.677
The sad part about it is,
when most people promise

590
00:31:09.701 --> 00:31:10.846
for better or for worse,

591
00:31:10.870 --> 00:31:13.310
they really only
mean for the better.

592
00:31:15.807 --> 00:31:16.952
Catherine and I were in love

593
00:31:16.976 --> 00:31:18.887
when we got married,
but today, ahem,

594
00:31:18.911 --> 00:31:21.156
we're two very different
people, all right?

595
00:31:21.180 --> 00:31:22.724
It's just not working
out anymore.

596
00:31:26.986 --> 00:31:30.354
Caleb, salt and pepper
are completely different.

597
00:31:31.723 --> 00:31:34.802
Their makeup is different,
their taste and their color.

598
00:31:34.826 --> 00:31:36.905
But you always see 'em together.

599
00:31:36.929 --> 00:31:39.975
And when you...

600
00:31:39.999 --> 00:31:41.331
Hold on just a second.

601
00:31:49.108 --> 00:31:50.385
What are you doing?

602
00:31:53.345 --> 00:31:54.322
Michael.

603
00:31:54.346 --> 00:31:56.091
Hey.

604
00:31:56.115 --> 00:31:58.181
What'd you do that for?

605
00:32:04.056 --> 00:32:06.701
Caleb, when two
people get married,

606
00:32:06.725 --> 00:32:08.836
it's for better or for worse.

607
00:32:08.860 --> 00:32:10.906
For richer or for poorer.

608
00:32:10.930 --> 00:32:14.075
In sickness and in health.

609
00:32:14.099 --> 00:32:15.076
I know that.

610
00:32:15.100 --> 00:32:16.511
But marriages aren't fireproof.

611
00:32:16.535 --> 00:32:18.201
Sometimes, you get burned.

612
00:32:20.005 --> 00:32:23.118
Fireproof doesn't mean
that a fire will never come,

613
00:32:23.142 --> 00:32:25.420
but that when it comes,
you'll be able to withstand it.

614
00:32:26.812 --> 00:32:28.390
You didn't have to
glue 'em together.

615
00:32:28.414 --> 00:32:31.026
Don't do it, Caleb. If
you pull 'em apart now,

616
00:32:31.050 --> 00:32:33.450
you'll break either
one or both of 'em.

617
00:32:35.955 --> 00:32:38.699
I am not a perfect person,
but better than most.

618
00:32:38.723 --> 00:32:41.702
And if my marriage is
failing, it is not all my fault.

619
00:32:41.726 --> 00:32:44.172
But, Caleb, man, I've seen
you run into a burning building

620
00:32:44.196 --> 00:32:46.141
to save people you
don't even know,

621
00:32:46.165 --> 00:32:47.809
but you're gonna let
your own marriage

622
00:32:47.833 --> 00:32:49.166
just burn to the ground.

623
00:32:52.271 --> 00:32:54.482
Michael, you are my friend.

624
00:32:54.506 --> 00:32:57.518
And I have allowed you to
speak freely with me on this job.

625
00:32:57.542 --> 00:32:58.842
Don't abuse it.

626
00:33:43.455 --> 00:33:47.668
<i>My son, this 40-day journey
cannot be taken lightly.</i>

627
00:33:47.692 --> 00:33:50.771
<i>It is a challenging and
often difficult process</i>

628
00:33:50.795 --> 00:33:53.041
<i>but an incredibly
fulfilling one.</i>

629
00:33:53.065 --> 00:33:56.144
<i>If you will commit to a
day at a time for 40 days,</i>

630
00:33:56.168 --> 00:33:59.780
<i>the results could change
your life and your marriage.</i>

631
00:33:59.804 --> 00:34:04.041
<i>Consider it a dare from others
who have done it before you.</i>

632
00:34:05.110 --> 00:34:06.321
<i>Day one:</i>

633
00:34:06.345 --> 00:34:08.623
<i>The first part of this
dare is fairly simple.</i>

634
00:34:08.647 --> 00:34:11.292
<i>Although love is communicated
in a number of ways,</i>

635
00:34:11.316 --> 00:34:14.562
<i>our words often reflect
the condition of our heart.</i>

636
00:34:14.586 --> 00:34:16.064
<i>For the next day, resolve to say</i>

637
00:34:16.088 --> 00:34:18.799
<i>nothing negative
to your spouse at all.</i>

638
00:34:18.823 --> 00:34:21.702
<i>If the temptation arises,
choose not to say anything.</i>

639
00:34:21.726 --> 00:34:23.071
<i>It's better to hold your tongue</i>

640
00:34:23.095 --> 00:34:25.273
<i>than to say
something you'll regret.</i>

641
00:34:25.297 --> 00:34:29.344
<i>Be quick to listen, slow to
speak and slow to get angry.</i>

642
00:34:29.368 --> 00:34:33.181
<i>James 1:19.</i>

643
00:34:45.984 --> 00:34:49.264
Would you have time to take
that to the dry-cleaners today?

644
00:34:49.288 --> 00:34:50.432
Think after two days off,

645
00:34:50.456 --> 00:34:52.522
you would have already
taken care of that.

646
00:35:07.106 --> 00:35:08.283
<i>Day two:</i>

647
00:35:08.307 --> 00:35:10.385
<i>It is difficult to
demonstrate love</i>

648
00:35:10.409 --> 00:35:12.687
<i>when you feel little
to no motivation.</i>

649
00:35:12.711 --> 00:35:16.191
<i>But love in its truest sense
is not based on feelings,</i>

650
00:35:16.215 --> 00:35:19.026
<i>but a determination to
show thoughtful actions</i>

651
00:35:19.050 --> 00:35:21.529
<i>even when there
seems to be no reward.</i>

652
00:35:21.553 --> 00:35:24.566
<i>In addition to saying nothing
negative to your spouse today,</i>

653
00:35:24.590 --> 00:35:27.768
<i>do at least one
unexpected gesture</i>

654
00:35:27.792 --> 00:35:30.227
<i>as an act of kindness.</i>

655
00:35:55.053 --> 00:35:57.365
I poured your coffee.

656
00:35:57.389 --> 00:35:59.501
I don't have time for coffee.

657
00:36:21.647 --> 00:36:23.324
<i>Day three:</i>

658
00:36:23.348 --> 00:36:27.228
<i>Whatever you put your
time, energy and money into</i>

659
00:36:27.252 --> 00:36:28.996
<i>will become more
important to you.</i>

660
00:36:29.020 --> 00:36:30.365
<i>It's hard to care for something</i>

661
00:36:30.389 --> 00:36:32.233
<i>you're not investing in.</i>

662
00:36:32.257 --> 00:36:35.370
<i>Along with refraining from
any negative comments,</i>

663
00:36:35.394 --> 00:36:36.837
<i>buy your wife
something that says</i>

664
00:36:36.861 --> 00:36:40.375
<i>you were thinking of her today.</i>

665
00:36:40.399 --> 00:36:42.644
Yeah, I need to order
some flowers or something

666
00:36:42.668 --> 00:36:43.978
for my wife.

667
00:36:44.002 --> 00:36:46.914
No. No, it doesn't matter.

668
00:36:46.938 --> 00:36:49.517
Sure. How much does that cost?

669
00:36:49.541 --> 00:36:51.553
Forty-five?

670
00:36:51.577 --> 00:36:54.189
Do you have something cheaper?

671
00:36:54.213 --> 00:36:56.057
Yeah, yeah, that...
That's more like it.

672
00:36:56.081 --> 00:36:57.958
Let's go with the 25.

673
00:36:57.982 --> 00:36:59.093
How about, um...?

674
00:36:59.117 --> 00:37:01.062
How about a box of
chocolates or something?

675
00:37:01.086 --> 00:37:02.497
How much is that?

676
00:37:02.521 --> 00:37:03.698
Oh.

677
00:37:03.722 --> 00:37:06.267
You're killing me.

678
00:37:06.291 --> 00:37:08.102
That's better.

679
00:37:08.126 --> 00:37:10.871
Okay, how about...? How
about a little stuffed bear?

680
00:37:10.895 --> 00:37:12.940
All right, forget the bear.

681
00:37:12.964 --> 00:37:14.442
Okay, how long
is it gonna take you

682
