that could do that, man.

701
00:38:12.391 --> 00:38:13.701
Not from this station.

702
00:38:13.725 --> 00:38:14.769
Tom McBride could.

703
00:38:14.793 --> 00:38:16.704
At Station 4? Are you kidding?

704
00:38:16.728 --> 00:38:19.106
He might do it in two and a
half but he can't do it under two.

705
00:38:19.130 --> 00:38:20.875
I don't know. Captain,

706
00:38:20.899 --> 00:38:23.378
he's strong, but
he's not as fast.

707
00:38:23.402 --> 00:38:25.882
I could take him
any day of the week.

708
00:38:26.805 --> 00:38:28.716
Wayne, you seem
pretty high on yourself.

709
00:38:28.740 --> 00:38:30.585
I think confidence
is a good thing,

710
00:38:30.609 --> 00:38:32.754
but you're over the top.

711
00:38:32.778 --> 00:38:34.322
Man, he way over the top.

712
00:38:34.346 --> 00:38:36.786
I can back it up.
That's all I'm saying.

713
00:38:37.215 --> 00:38:38.459
Wrath of God, baby.

714
00:38:38.483 --> 00:38:40.094
What's that for?

715
00:38:40.118 --> 00:38:41.763
We're about to
have a little contest.

716
00:38:41.787 --> 00:38:44.532
