00:40:30.562 --> 00:40:33.107
Sure, and congratulations on
your cancer-research award.

759
00:40:33.131 --> 00:40:34.675
You deserve it.
I appreciate that.

760
00:40:36.067 --> 00:40:37.512
This is Catherine.

761
00:40:37.536 --> 00:40:39.514
Hey, it's Caleb.

762
00:40:39.538 --> 00:40:41.181
I wanted to call
and check on you.

763
00:40:41.205 --> 00:40:44.018
You wanted to check on me?

764
00:40:44.042 --> 00:40:45.185
What for?

765
00:40:45.209 --> 00:40:48.611
Uh, you know, just see
if you needed anything.

766
00:40:50.148 --> 00:40:52.293
You called to see if
I needed anything?

767
00:40:52.317 --> 00:40:53.795
<i>Right, yeah.</i>

768
00:40:53.819 --> 00:40:56.063
<i>Uh, you want me to bring
something home for you, or...?</i>

769
00:40:56.087 --> 00:40:58.933
<i>Or get something from
the store in the morning?</i>

770
00:40:58.957 --> 00:41:01.769
Caleb, you never asked me
this before. What's going on?

771
00:41:01.793 --> 00:41:05.740
I just wanted to see if you
needed anything, that's it.

772
00:41:05.764 --> 00:41:08.075
<i>I'm fine.</i>

773
00:41:08.099 --> 00:41:10.277
Okay.

774
00:41:10.301 --> 00:41:12.480
All right, well...

775
00:41:12.504 --> 00:41:14.070
goodbye.

776
00:41:19.978 --> 00:41:22.311
Day four, ahem, done.

777
00:41:27.719 --> 00:41:30.197
Hey, Cat, how you doing, girl?

778
00:41:30.221 --> 00:41:32.166
Confused.

779
00:41:32.190 --> 00:41:34.168
Uh, my husband's acting weird.

780
00:41:34.192 --> 00:41:35.636
What's he doing?

781
00:41:35.660 --> 00:41:37.071
Well...

782
00:41:38.096 --> 00:41:39.674
in the last few days,

783
00:41:39.698 --> 00:41:42.209
he has fixed me coffee,

784
00:41:42.233 --> 00:41:45.045
bought me these
pitiful little flowers

785
00:41:45.069 --> 00:41:48.483
and just now, called just
to see if I'm doing okay.

786
00:41:48.507 --> 00:41:49.650
Really?

787
00:41:49.674 --> 00:41:50.952
Yeah.

788
00:41:50.976 --> 00:41:52.520
I'll tell you what he's doing.

789
00:41:52.544 --> 00:41:54.421
He's trying to butter
you up for a divorce.

790
00:41:54.445 --> 00:41:56.491
And why would he do that?

791
00:41:56.515 --> 00:41:58.192
Before my cousin
Luwanna got a divorce,

792
00:41:58.216 --> 00:41:59.794
her husband did the same thing.

793
00:41:59.818 --> 00:42:01.428
He started acting
all nice and sweet,

794
00:42:01.452 --> 00:42:02.997
and then the next thing we know,

795
00:42:03.021 --> 00:42:05.199
he walks away with the
house and most of their money.

796
00:42:05.223 --> 00:42:07.001
He hasn't even
talked to her since.

797
00:42:07.025 --> 00:42:09.504
Don't you let him
deceive you, girl.

798
00:42:09.528 --> 00:42:10.693
Mm.

799
00:42:36.721 --> 00:42:39.567
Did you clear your history?

800
00:42:39.591 --> 00:42:41.168
What?

801
00:42:41.192 --> 00:42:42.469
Did you wipe the websites off

802
00:42:42.493 --> 00:42:45.028
so nobody would see
where you've been?

803
00:42:50.602 --> 00:42:52.813
You know, Caleb, you're
not fooling anybody.

804
00:42:52.837 --> 00:42:54.515
I know exactly what
you're trying to do,

805
00:42:54.539 --> 00:42:58.252
buying me flowers
and calling me at work.

806
00:42:58.276 --> 00:42:59.720
And what is that?

807
00:42:59.744 --> 00:43:01.288
I'm meeting with a
lawyer next week,

808
00:43:01.312 --> 00:43:02.757
and don't you
think for one second

809
00:43:02.781 --> 00:43:05.526
I'm buying into this
nice-guy routine.

810
00:43:05.550 --> 00:43:08.896
What are you talking about?

811
00:43:08.920 --> 00:43:11.198
You're not getting one
dime more than you deserve.

812
00:43:11.222 --> 00:43:14.201
When this divorce is
final, I'm taking my share.

813
00:43:14.225 --> 00:43:15.937
Is that what you
think I'm doing?

814
00:43:15.961 --> 00:43:17.939
No, I know that's
what you're doing.

815
00:43:17.963 --> 00:43:19.239
Yeah, well, you're wrong.

816
00:43:19.263 --> 00:43:20.875
You never assume
I would do anything

817
00:43:20.899 --> 00:43:22.977
worthy of respect.
Anything honorable.

818
00:43:23.001 --> 00:43:24.244
Honorable?

819
00:43:24.268 --> 00:43:26.747
Honorable? What were
you just looking at, Caleb?

820
00:43:26.771 --> 00:43:28.248
What was on that
computer screen?

821
00:43:28.272 --> 00:43:30.250
Was that honorable?

822
00:43:30.274 --> 00:43:31.619
Who do you think you're fooling?

823
00:43:31.643 --> 00:43:33.420
Do you know why your
sweet little gestures

824
00:43:33.444 --> 00:43:34.922
mean nothing to me?

825
00:43:34.946 --> 00:43:37.224
It's because that's the
kind of man you've become.

826
00:43:37.248 --> 00:43:39.460
When you're alone,
that's what you default to,

827
00:43:39.484 --> 00:43:42.196
and there is nothing
honorable about it.

828
00:44:09.614 --> 00:44:10.654
Mr. Rudolph.

829
00:44:12.250 --> 00:44:13.983
Caleb.

830
00:44:30.368 --> 00:44:31.345
Hello?

831
00:44:31.369 --> 00:44:32.880
It's not working, Dad.

832
00:44:32.904 --> 00:44:34.115
<i>What's not working?</i>

833
00:44:34.139 --> 00:44:36.651
This whole love dare
thing. It is not working.

834
00:44:36.675 --> 00:44:38.953
Tell me what's going on.

835
00:44:38.977 --> 00:44:41.522
I have been doing
everything that it says to do,

836
00:44:41.546 --> 00:44:44.458
and she has completely
rejected all of it.

837
00:44:44.482 --> 00:44:46.426
Caleb, this process
takes 40 days, not four.

838
00:44:46.450 --> 00:44:48.729
<i>What's the point of going
down a dead-end road</i>

839
00:44:48.753 --> 00:44:50.397
<i>when you know it's
not going anywhere?</i>

840
00:44:50.421 --> 00:44:52.166
You don't know that yet.

841
00:44:52.190 --> 00:44:54.035
<i>Caleb, you're not a quitter.</i>

842
00:44:54.059 --> 00:44:59.040
And something tells me you're
doing just enough to get by.

843
00:44:59.064 --> 00:45:00.596
Am I right?

844
00:45:06.270 --> 00:45:07.848
I feel nothing.

845
00:45:07.872 --> 00:45:09.516
I understand, son.

846
00:45:09.540 --> 00:45:12.153
<i>But this is not
based on feelings.</i>

847
00:45:12.177 --> 00:45:13.620
<i>It's a decision.</i>

848
00:45:13.644 --> 00:45:15.923
You can't give up yet.

849
00:45:15.947 --> 00:45:18.147
Keep taking a day at a time.

850
00:45:20.318 --> 00:45:21.295
Tsk.

851
00:45:21.319 --> 00:45:22.418
Yes, sir.

852
00:45:23.487 --> 00:45:24.987
I love you, son.

853
00:45:26.057 --> 00:45:27.656
You too, Dad.

854
00:45:36.300 --> 00:45:38.713
How is he?

855
00:45:38.737 --> 00:45:41.437
We've gotta start
praying for him more.

856
00:45:44.508 --> 00:45:47.176
Mama, I don't know what to do.

857
00:45:48.346 --> 00:45:50.024
I know you always
told me to hang on

858
00:45:50.048 --> 00:45:52.882
during the hard times, but...

859
00:45:56.221 --> 00:46:00.300
You don't know what
I've been competing with.

860
00:46:00.324 --> 00:46:02.191
I mean, when he look...

861
00:46:08.266 --> 00:46:12.246
He makes me feel so humiliated.

862
00:46:13.271 --> 00:46:15.805
And he doesn't even know it.

863
00:46:19.443 --> 00:46:23.545
When did I stop being
good enough for him?

864
00:46:49.908 --> 00:46:52.719
<i>♪ It's a slow fade ♪</i>

865
00:46:52.743 --> 00:46:55.890
<i>♪ When you give yourself away ♪</i>

866
00:46:55.914 --> 00:46:59.193
<i>♪ It's a slow fade ♪</i>

867
00:46:59.217 --> 00:47:01.962
<i>♪ When black and white
Have turned to gray ♪</i>

868
00:47:01.986 --> 00:47:05.399
<i>♪ Thoughts invade ♪</i>

869
00:47:05.423 --> 00:47:08.502
<i>♪ Choices are made ♪</i>

870
00:47:08.526 --> 00:47:11.138
<i>♪ A price will be paid ♪</i>

871
00:47:11.162 --> 00:47:14.675
<i>♪ When you give yourself away ♪</i>

872
00:47:14.699 --> 00:47:19.468
<i>♪ People never
crumble In a day ♪</i>

873
00:47:20.538 --> 00:47:24.040
<i>♪ It's a slow fade ♪</i>

874
00:47:27.145 --> 00:47:31.214
<i>♪ It's a slow fade ♪</i>

875
00:47:35.854 --> 00:47:37.019
So, what day are you on?

876
00:47:39.157 --> 00:47:41.123
Eighteen. And?

877
00:47:42.626 --> 00:47:44.205
And it's still difficult.

878
00:47:44.229 --> 00:47:48.008
Every day has me adding a
new concept to the way I treat her.

879
00:47:48.032 --> 00:47:49.710
For example?

880
00:47:49.734 --> 00:47:52.479
Well, here.

881
00:47:52.503 --> 00:47:54.614
Day 16 was about
praying for her.

882
00:47:54.638 --> 00:47:55.816
I kind of skipped that one.

883
00:47:55.840 --> 00:47:59.720
Day 17 is about
listening to her.

884
00:47:59.744 --> 00:48:02.156
Eighteen's about
studying her again.

885
00:48:02.180 --> 00:48:04.358
Studying her? Yeah.

886
00:48:04.382 --> 00:48:06.460
Here.

887
00:48:06.484 --> 00:48:08.462
"When a man is trying to
win the heart of a woman,

888
00:48:08.486 --> 00:48:09.796
"he studies her.

889
00:48:09.820 --> 00:48:12.532
"He learns her likes,
dislikes, habits and hobbies.

890
00:48:12.556 --> 00:48:14.935
"But after he wins her
heart and marries her,

891
00:48:14.959 --> 00:48:16.636
"he often stops
learning about her.

892
00:48:16.660 --> 00:48:19.073
"If the amount he studied
her before marriage

893
00:48:19.097 --> 00:48:21.141
"was equal to a
high school degree,

894
00:48:21.165 --> 00:48:23.010
"he should continue
to learn about her

895
00:48:23.034 --> 00:48:26.213
"until he gains a college
degree, a master's degree

896
00:48:26.237 --> 00:48:28.415
"and ultimately, a
doctorate degree.

897
00:48:28.439 --> 00:48:30.617
"It is a lifelong journey
that draws his heart

898
00:48:30.641 --> 00:48:33.687
ever closer to hers."
That's a pretty good concept.

899
00:48:33.711 --> 00:48:35.511
I never thought
about it like that.

900
00:48:37.916 --> 00:48:40.327
So do you study Tina?

901
00:48:40.351 --> 00:48:43.085
Yeah, but I don't think I got
my college degree on her yet.

902
00:48:44.923 --> 00:48:47.868
So tell me a little bit more
about the studying her.

903
00:48:47.892 --> 00:48:50.971
Ah, I'm supposed to, uh,
make her a candlelight dinner,

904
00:48:50.995 --> 00:48:53.440
and then ask her a
whole list of questions.

905
00:48:53.464 --> 00:48:55.943
Well, my advice is go all out.

906
00:48:55.967 --> 00:48:57.278
Meaning?

907
00:48:57.302 --> 00:48:58.645
Don't go cheap.

908
00:48:58.669 --> 00:49:00.847
If you don't cook, get it
from a good restaurant.

909
00:49:00.871 --> 00:49:02.649
Take it home, use
your best dishes,

910
00:49:02.673 --> 00:49:05.386
glasses, music, everything.

911
00:49:05.410 --> 00:49:07.343
Make it a memorable date.

912
00:49:10.048 --> 00:49:12.026
Man, what you talking about?

913
00:49:12.050 --> 00:49:13.527
You ain't had a date in a year.

914
00:49:13.551 --> 00:49:15.362
I'm like a fine wine.

915
00:49:15.386 --> 00:49:17.831
I need about 35 years
to reach perfection.

916
00:49:17.855 --> 00:49:19.633
But the lady that
gets Wayne Floyd,

917
00:49:19.657 --> 00:49:21.468
she'll get the complete package.

918
00:49:21.492 --> 00:49:22.702
You mean complete wreckage.

919
00:49:22.726 --> 00:49:23.737
No.

920
00:49:23.761 --> 00:49:26.907
I'm 255 pounds of pure love.

921
00:49:26.931 --> 00:49:28.475
All you need to
make marriage work

922
00:49:28.499 --> 00:49:30.010
is a little bit of romance.

923
00:49:30.034 --> 00:49:31.878
And that comes from right here.

924
00:49:31.902 --> 00:49:35.115
Man, that's easy to say when
you ain't never been married.

925
00:49:35.139 --> 00:49:36.883
It's a lot harder
than you think, man.

926
00:49:36.907 --> 00:49:39.753
One day I'm gonna walk in here
with a tanned beauty on my arm.

927
00:49:39.777 --> 00:49:41.322
I'll show you how
easy it can be.

928
00:49:41.346 --> 00:49:43.324
Man, the only thing
you'll come in here with

929
00:49:43.348 --> 00:49:45.348
hanging from your arm
is a bucket of chicken.

930
00:49:48.152 --> 00:49:49.986
It was tomato juice.

931
00:50:02.400 --> 00:50:05.245
Tomato juice? Man, that's wrong!

932
00:50:05.269 --> 00:50:08.048
That's wrong. What's wrong?

933
00:50:08.072 --> 00:50:10.484
I drank the real stuff and
he drank tomato juice?

934
00:50:10.508 --> 00:50:11.618
You just got that?

935
00:50:11.642 --> 00:50:13.253
Do you know what
that stuff did to me?

936
00:50:13.277 --> 00:50:14.989
Go to bed, Wayne.

937
00:50:15.013 --> 00:50:17.157
There's some
serious repercussions!

938
00:50:17.181 --> 00:50:18.859
Quiet.

939
00:50:18.883 --> 00:50:21.828
Oh, it's on now.

940
00:50:21.852 --> 00:50:24.231
Done lit a fuse.

941
00:50:24.255 --> 00:50:27.089
Somebody's gonna get
a karate-chop sandwich.

942
00:51:42.866 --> 00:51:44.066
What are you doing?

943
00:51:47.271 --> 00:51:49.671
Maybe I'd like to have
dinner with my wife.

944
00:51:55.580 --> 00:51:57.900
Let me be real clear
with you about something.

945
00:52:00.684 --> 00:52:03.397
I do not love you.

946
00:52:48.932 --> 00:52:51.445
Oh, son.

947
00:52:51.469 --> 00:52:53.902
This is when it gets hard.

948
00:52:55.306 --> 00:52:56.450
Hello, Caleb.

949
00:52:56.474 --> 00:52:57.851
We're done, Dad.

950
00:52:57.875 --> 00:52:59.319
I am not gonna keep doing this.

951
00:52:59.343 --> 00:53:02.122
I have tried and
there's nothing there.

952
00:53:02.146 --> 00:53:03.457
It's not worth it.

953
00:53:03.481 --> 00:53:06.059
I understand, son, but
you're halfway there,

954
00:53:06.083 --> 00:53:08.128
which was the most
difficult for us too.

955
00:53:08.152 --> 00:53:11.097
But at least you had some
hope. She has given me nothing.

956
00:53:11.121 --> 00:53:13.321
<i>There was a point when
we had no hope either.</i>

957
00:53:14.091 --> 00:53:16.336
Our marriage should
have ended, Caleb.

958
00:53:16.360 --> 00:53:18.772
You can't listen to the
way you feel at the moment.

959
00:53:18.796 --> 00:53:20.474
<i>There's no doubt
she's seen you trying.</i>

960
00:53:20.498 --> 00:53:22.108
No, she doesn't care, Dad.

961
00:53:22.132 --> 00:53:24.978
None of this means
anything to her.

962
00:53:25.002 --> 00:53:26.502
Dad, I tried.

963
00:53:28.206 --> 00:53:29.505
Caleb, are you off tomorrow?

964
00:53:30.408 --> 00:53:31.585
Yeah, why?

965
00:53:31.609 --> 00:53:34.510
I'm coming to see
you. We can talk then.

966
00:53:35.846 --> 00:53:37.624
Dad, you don't have to do that.

967
00:53:37.648 --> 00:53:41.116
I want to, son.
I'd like to come.

968
00:53:43.221 --> 00:53:45.020
All right.

969
00:54:11.749 --> 00:54:13.460
Dad, I gotta be honest with you.

970
00:54:13.484 --> 00:54:17.063
I feel bad that you drove four
hours just to come see me.

971
00:54:17.087 --> 00:54:20.834
It was good. It gave me
time to think and pray.

972
00:54:20.858 --> 00:54:23.803
So, uh, what are you on, Day 20?

973
00:54:23.827 --> 00:54:25.739
Yeah, yeah, something like that.

974
00:54:25.763 --> 00:54:29.376
Yeah. I'd say the halfway
point was the hardest for us.

975
00:54:29.400 --> 00:54:31.511
Why?

976
00:54:31.535 --> 00:54:33.714
Well, it's when you determine

977
00:54:33.738 --> 00:54:35.349
whether your
heart's in it or not.

978
00:54:35.373 --> 00:54:36.850
Makes you check
your real motives

979
00:54:36.874 --> 00:54:39.386
when things get difficult.

980
00:54:39.410 --> 00:54:41.622
Yeah? Did Mom
give you a hard time?

981
00:54:41.646 --> 00:54:45.626
No. I thought your mother had
a pretty good attitude about it.

982
00:54:45.650 --> 00:54:48.027
Yeah, well, Catherine's
not buying any of it.

983
00:54:48.051 --> 00:54:49.263
Why do you think that is?

984
00:54:49.287 --> 00:54:50.930
Because she doesn't love me.

985
00:54:50.954 --> 00:54:52.366
She doesn't even like me.

986
00:54:52.390 --> 00:54:56.270
Dad, she's just about
ignored everything I've done.

987
00:54:56.294 --> 00:54:58.960
Are you reading
everything on each page?

988
00:55:00.698 --> 00:55:03.009
You mean the Bible
verses at the bottom of it?

989
00:55:03.033 --> 00:55:05.011
No, I'm not, Dad. I...

990
00:55:05.035 --> 00:55:07.147
I told you, that is
not what I need.

991
00:55:07.171 --> 00:55:08.782
And what do you need?

992
00:55:08.806 --> 00:55:10.584
I need Catherine to
wake up to the fact

993
00:55:10.608 --> 00:55:13.487
that we are about to
get an ugly divorce.

994
00:55:13.511 --> 00:55:16.990
And I'm trying to prevent that,
but I cannot do it by myself.

995
00:55:17.014 --> 00:55:20.015
That may be true, but I
think you need more than that.

996
00:55:22.186 --> 00:55:24.731
Dad, if you're gonna tell me
I need Jesus, please don't.

997
00:55:24.755 --> 00:55:27.401
I... I don't need a
crutch to get through life.

998
00:55:27.425 --> 00:55:29.736
Oh, son, Jesus is
much more than a crutch.

999
00:55:29.760 --> 00:55:33.106
He's become the most
significant part of our lives.

1000
00:55:33.130 --> 00:55:34.808
Dad, why do you
keep saying that?

1001
00:55:34.832 --> 00:55:38.111
He's the most significant
part? How...? How is that?

1002
00:55:38.135 --> 00:55:43.317
When I realized who I
was and who he was,

1003
00:55:43.341 --> 00:55:45.485
I realized my need for him.

1004
00:55:45.509 --> 00:55:48.477
I needed his
forgiveness and salvation.

1005
00:55:50.013 --> 00:55:52.359
See, I... I don't
understand that.

1006
00:55:52.383 --> 00:55:53.893
Why do I need his salvation?

1007
00:55:53.917 --> 00:55:56.330
What, am I gonna
be thrown into hell?

1008
00:55:56.354 --> 00:55:59.733
For what? Because
I got divorced?

1009
00:55:59.757 --> 00:56:01.435
No.

1010
00:56:01.459 --> 00:56:03.903
Because you
violated his standards.

1011
00:56:03.927 --> 00:56:06.707
What? Thou shall not kill?

1012
00:56:06.731 --> 00:56:09.142
Dad, I help people.
I am a good person.

1013
00:56:09.166 --> 00:56:10.777
According to you.

1014
00:56:10.801 --> 00:56:13.513
But God doesn't judge
by your standards.

1015
00:56:13.537 --> 00:56:14.748
He uses his.

1016
00:56:14.772 --> 00:56:15.782
And what are his?

1017
00:56:15.806 --> 00:56:18.218
Well, truth.

1018
00:56:18.242 --> 00:56:19.419
Okay. Love.

1019
00:56:19.443 --> 00:56:21.254
I'm honest. Faithfulness.

1020
00:56:21.278 --> 00:56:23.890
I care about people.
I am those things.

1021
00:56:23.914 --> 00:56:25.492
Sometimes.

1022
00:56:25.516 --> 00:56:30.564
But have you loved God,
the one who gave you life?

1023
00:56:30.588 --> 00:56:36.102
His standards are so high, he
considers hatred to be murder

1024
00:56:36.126 --> 00:56:40.161
and lust to be adultery.

1025
00:56:43.834 --> 00:56:47.146
Oh, Dad, what about
all the good I've done?

1026
00:56:47.170 --> 00:56:49.115
Son, saving someone from a fire

1027
00:56:49.139 --> 00:56:50.817
does not make
you right with God.

1028
00:56:50.841 --> 00:56:53.387
You've broken his commandments.

1029
00:56:53.411 --> 00:56:55.977
And one day, you'll
answer to him for that.

1030
00:57:04.087 --> 00:57:06.032
Caleb,

1031
00:57:06.056 --> 00:57:08.602
if I were to ask you why you're
so frustrated with Catherine,

1032
00:57:08.626 --> 00:57:09.925
what would you say?

1033
00:57:14.799 --> 00:57:16.710
She's stubborn.

1034
00:57:16.734 --> 00:57:19.579
She makes everything
difficult for me.

1035
00:57:19.603 --> 00:57:21.415
She's ungrateful.

1036
00:57:21.439 --> 00:57:24.150
She's constantly
griping about something.

1037
00:57:24.174 --> 00:57:26.753
Has she thanked you for anything
you've done the last 20 days?

1038
00:57:26.777 --> 00:57:27.821
No.

1039
00:57:27.845 --> 00:57:30.256
And you'd think
after I washed the car,

1040
00:57:30.280 --> 00:57:32.692
I've changed the oil, do
the dishes, clean the house,

1041
00:57:32.716 --> 00:57:36.563
that she would try to show
me a little bit of gratitude.

1042
00:57:36.587 --> 00:57:38.364
Well, she doesn't.

1043
00:57:38.388 --> 00:57:39.499
In fact, when I come home,

1044
00:57:39.523 --> 00:57:42.502
she makes me feel
like I'm an enemy.

1045
00:57:42.526 --> 00:57:44.571
I'm not even welcome
in my own home, Dad.

1046
00:57:44.595 --> 00:57:46.940
That is what
really ticks me off.

1047
00:57:46.964 --> 00:57:48.207
Dad, for the last three weeks,

1048
00:57:48.231 --> 00:57:50.343
I have bent over
backwards for her.

1049
00:57:50.367 --> 00:57:51.812
I have tried to demonstrate

1050
00:57:51.836 --> 00:57:54.280
that I still care about
this relationship.

1051
00:57:54.304 --> 00:57:57.150
I bought her flowers,
which she threw away.

1052
00:57:57.174 --> 00:57:59.352
I have taken her
insults and her sarcasm,

1053
00:57:59.376 --> 00:58:00.987
but last night was it.

1054
00:58:01.011 --> 00:58:02.088
I made dinner for her,

1055
00:58:02.112 --> 00:58:04.891
I did everything I
could to demonstrate

1056
00:58:04.915 --> 00:58:07.694
that I care about her,
to show value for her,

1057
00:58:07.718 --> 00:58:09.429
and she spat in my face.

1058
00:58:09.453 --> 00:58:13.132
She does not deserve this,
Dad. I am not doing it anymore.

1059
00:58:13.156 --> 00:58:15.435
How am I supposed to
show love to somebody

1060
00:58:15.459 --> 00:58:19.461
over and over and over,
who constantly rejects me?

1061
00:58:23.701 --> 00:58:25.133
That's a good question.

1062
00:58:34.945 --> 00:58:37.078
Dad, that is not what I'm doing.

1063
00:58:38.015 --> 00:58:40.293
Isn't it?

1064
00:58:40.317 --> 00:58:41.862
No...

1065
00:58:41.886 --> 00:58:43.797
Dad, that is not
what this is about.

1066
00:58:43.821 --> 00:58:46.199
Son, you just asked me:

1067
00:58:46.223 --> 00:58:48.468
"How can someone show
love over and over again,

1068
00:58:48.492 --> 00:58:51.571
when they're
constantly rejected?"

1069
00:58:51.595 --> 00:58:53.840
Caleb, the answer is:

1070
00:58:53.864 --> 00:58:55.642
You can't love her,

1071
00:58:55.666 --> 00:58:58.667
because you can't give
her what you don't have.

1072
00:59:02.272 --> 00:59:03.750
I couldn't truly
love your mother

1073
00:59:03.774 --> 00:59:06.254
till I understood
what love really was.

1074
00:59:07.277 --> 00:59:10.891
It's not because I get
some reward out of it.

1075
00:59:10.915 --> 00:59:13.226
I've now made a decision
to love your mother

1076
00:59:13.250 --> 00:59:15.490
whether she deserves it or not.

1077
00:59:16.887 --> 00:59:20.288
Son, God loves you even
though you don't deserve it.

1078
00:59:21.391 --> 00:59:24.337
Even though you've rejected him.

1079
00:59:24.361 --> 00:59:26.094
Spat in his face.

1080
00:59:28.098 --> 00:59:30.243
God sent Jesus
to die on the cross

1081
00:59:30.267 --> 00:59:33.046
and take the
punishment for your sin

1082
00:59:33.070 --> 00:59:35.537
because he loves you.

1083
00:59:36.907 --> 00:59:40.576
The cross was offensive
to me until I came to it.

1084
00:59:41.912 --> 00:59:43.178
But when I did,

1085
00:59:45.482 --> 00:59:47.794
Jesus Christ changed my life.

1086
00:59:47.818 --> 00:59:50.986
That's when I truly
began to love your mom.

1087
00:59:53.190 --> 00:59:56.903
Son, I can't
settle this for you.

1088
00:59:56.927 --> 00:59:59.573
This is between
you and the Lord.

1089
00:59:59.597 --> 01:00:03.031
But I love you too much
not to tell you the truth.

1090
01:00:04.902 --> 01:00:07.836
Can't you see that you need him?

1091
01:00:13.911 --> 01:00:17.312
Can't you see that you
need his forgiveness?

1092
01:00:21.719 --> 01:00:22.719
Yes.

1093
01:00:25.923 --> 01:00:28.423
Will you trust
him with your life?

1094
01:00:58.022 --> 01:01:00.466
Waffle time.

1095
01:01:00.490 --> 01:01:02.969
Hey, man, I'd like to talk
to you about something.

1096
01:01:02.993 --> 01:01:04.904
What's that?

1097
01:01:04.928 --> 01:01:07.488
Well... Hey, captain.

1098
01:01:07.965 --> 01:01:10.810
I think B shift is trying
to pull a joke on us, man.

1099
01:01:10.834 --> 01:01:12.812
Salt and pepper
shaker won't come apart.

1100
01:01:12.836 --> 01:01:14.502
Hey, toss them over here.

1101
01:01:16.173 --> 01:01:18.985
Thanks, man. Don't forget to
mop the kitchen after breakfast.

1102
01:01:19.009 --> 01:01:20.341
Yes, sir.

1103
01:01:22.780 --> 01:01:23.912
You wanna tell me something?

1104
01:01:26.516 --> 01:01:28.684
Uh, it's about your faith.

1105
01:01:29.720 --> 01:01:30.964
My faith?

1106
01:01:30.988 --> 01:01:32.098
Yeah.

1107
01:01:32.122 --> 01:01:34.567
What about it?

1108
01:01:34.591 --> 01:01:37.336
Well, I'm in.

1109
01:01:37.360 --> 01:01:38.805
You're in?

1110
01:01:38.829 --> 01:01:40.996
Yeah, I'm in.

1111
01:01:42.866 --> 01:01:44.744
Are you saying that
you wanna be in?

1112
01:01:44.768 --> 01:01:46.680
I'm saying I'm in.

1113
01:01:46.704 --> 01:01:48.614
You're really in? I'm really in.

1114
01:01:48.638 --> 01:01:50.516
'Cause you can't be
half in and say you're in.

1115
01:01:50.540 --> 01:01:53.519
You gotta be all in,
brother. I'm saying I'm all in.

1116
01:01:53.543 --> 01:01:55.488
Oh, Caleb, I can't
believe it, man!

1117
01:01:55.512 --> 01:01:57.757
Yeah. You're my brother.

1118
01:01:57.781 --> 01:01:59.059
I'm your brother? Yeah, man.

1119
01:01:59.083 --> 01:02:00.760
You're my brother
from another mother,

1120
01:02:00.784 --> 01:02:03.262
but now we got the same father.

1121
01:02:03.286 --> 01:02:05.331
What? I'll explain
it to you later, man.

1122
01:02:05.355 --> 01:02:06.933
This is awesome.

1123
01:02:06.957 --> 01:02:09.202
Does Catherine know? Uh, no.

1124
01:02:09.226 --> 01:02:11.004
No, I don't think
she'd care right now,

1125
01:02:11.028 --> 01:02:12.572
to tell you the truth.

1126
01:02:12.596 --> 01:02:16.009
She hasn't been taking too
well to this whole love dare thing.

1127
01:02:16.033 --> 01:02:17.310
But you're not done yet, right?

1128
01:02:17.334 --> 01:02:19.012
No, I'm day 21 out of 40.

1129
01:02:19.036 --> 01:02:21.948
But I'll be honest with
you. Up to this point,

1130
01:02:21.972 --> 01:02:24.684
my heart's not been in
it. That's what matters.

1131
01:02:24.708 --> 01:02:27.754
A woman can tell when you're
just going through the motions.

1132
01:02:27.778 --> 01:02:29.789
That's absolutely right.

1133
01:02:29.813 --> 01:02:31.057
Hey, let me ask you a question.

1134
01:02:31.081 --> 01:02:33.492
Go ahead.

1135
01:02:33.516 --> 01:02:35.595
How did you get off to
such a good start with Tina?

1136
01:02:35.619 --> 01:02:37.230
I mean, why is it
so easy for you?

1137
01:02:37.254 --> 01:02:40.366
Oh, it's not always been
easy. Marriage takes work, man.

1138
01:02:40.390 --> 01:02:43.770
Tina is an incredible wife.

1139
01:02:43.794 --> 01:02:45.914
But we learned a lot
of lessons the hard way.

1140
01:02:47.364 --> 01:02:48.674
Well,

1141
01:02:48.698 --> 01:02:50.999
at least you haven't
had to face divorce.

1142
01:02:54.037 --> 01:02:56.037
I wish that were true.

1143
01:02:57.174 --> 01:02:59.219
What does that mean?

1144
01:02:59.243 --> 01:03:01.524
You and Tina been
struggling that much?

1145
01:03:02.345 --> 01:03:05.680
Not me and Tina. But
I did with my first wife.

1146
01:03:10.254 --> 01:03:12.265
What?

1147
01:03:12.289 --> 01:03:14.768
You were married to
someone before Tina?

1148
01:03:14.792 --> 01:03:18.004
For one horrible year.

1149
01:03:18.028 --> 01:03:19.873
I got married for
the wrong reasons.

1150
01:03:19.897 --> 01:03:22.776
Then I turned around and got
a divorce for the wrong reasons.

1151
01:03:22.800 --> 01:03:27.180
Man, I thought I was
just following my heart.

1152
01:03:27.204 --> 01:03:29.149
Michael, I've worked
with you for five years.

1153
01:03:29.173 --> 01:03:30.250
You've never told me that.

1154
01:03:30.274 --> 01:03:31.572
Because I'm not proud of it.

1155
01:03:32.776 --> 01:03:34.988
It was before I gave
my life to the Lord,

1156
01:03:35.012 --> 01:03:36.823
and, man, I was just
only concerned about

1157
01:03:36.847 --> 01:03:38.180
my rights and my needs.

1158
01:03:39.183 --> 01:03:41.427
Man, I ruined her life.

1159
01:03:41.451 --> 01:03:44.831
But when I gave my life to God,

1160
01:03:44.855 --> 01:03:47.600
I tried to find her, but
she'd already remarried.

1161
01:03:47.624 --> 01:03:51.204
So believe me when I
tell you I got a big scar.

1162
01:03:51.228 --> 01:03:53.795
Man, God meant
marriage to be for life.

1163
01:03:55.632 --> 01:03:59.045
That's why you gotta keep
your vows to Catherine.

1164
01:03:59.069 --> 01:04:02.715
You gotta beg God to teach
you how to be a good husband.

1165
01:04:02.739 --> 01:04:04.417
And don't just follow
your heart, man,

1166
01:04:04.441 --> 01:04:06.452
because your heart
can be deceived.

1167
01:04:06.476 --> 01:04:10.712
But you gotta lead your heart.

1168
01:04:16.419 --> 01:04:18.965
It's just been hard
for me, you know?

1169
01:04:18.989 --> 01:04:21.309
I saw my parents
again yesterday,

1170
01:04:22.192 --> 01:04:25.471
and, well, Mom's
not doing too well.

1171
01:04:25.495 --> 01:04:29.709
It's amazing how much a
stroke can affect somebody's life.

1172
01:04:29.733 --> 01:04:31.377
I just...

1173
01:04:31.401 --> 01:04:33.913
I feel like she's
trapped, you know?

1174
01:04:33.937 --> 01:04:36.049
And Dad does his
best to communicate,

1175
01:04:36.073 --> 01:04:38.439
but it's hard for him too.

1176
01:04:40.443 --> 01:04:42.155
Catherine, I'm so sorry.

1177
01:04:42.179 --> 01:04:44.924
You seem very close to them.

1178
01:04:44.948 --> 01:04:46.148
I am.

1179
01:04:47.017 --> 01:04:48.561
They had me late
in life so it was like

1180
01:04:48.585 --> 01:04:50.363
growing up with grandparents.

1181
01:04:50.387 --> 01:04:51.797
So they spoiled you.

1182
01:04:51.821 --> 01:04:54.267
Hey, now. I think they
did a pretty good job.

1183
01:04:54.291 --> 01:04:56.691
They did. They
should be very proud.

1184
01:04:58.028 --> 01:05:00.974
You know, you're kind of
sweet when you wanna be.

1185
01:05:00.998 --> 01:05:02.141
Kind of?

1186
01:05:02.165 --> 01:05:04.077
Ha-ha. Well, with some training,

1187
01:05:04.101 --> 01:05:05.845
I think you could
be a fine gentleman.

1188
01:05:05.869 --> 01:05:07.302
Well, are you offering lessons?

1189
01:05:09.139 --> 01:05:12.318
So, what does your mom need?

1190
01:05:13.843 --> 01:05:16.756
Well, a better wheelchair
and hospital bed

1191
01:05:16.780 --> 01:05:18.958
would be at the top of the list.

1192
01:05:18.982 --> 01:05:22.595
I've been working with RMS
Medical Supplies to get them,

1193
01:05:22.619 --> 01:05:23.897
but it's so expensive.

1194
01:05:23.921 --> 01:05:26.221
Well, you can't put a
price on helping your mom.

1195
01:05:27.424 --> 01:05:29.769
That's right.

1196
01:05:29.793 --> 01:05:32.171
So it's worth the sacrifice.

1197
01:05:32.195 --> 01:05:34.996
You know, they're lucky
to have you for a daughter.

1198
01:05:37.567 --> 01:05:40.013
Don't look at me like that.
I'm trying to help you out.

1199
01:05:40.037 --> 01:05:41.781
Why does it matter
what my bed looks like?

1200
01:05:41.805 --> 01:05:43.182
I'm the one that sleeps in it.

1201
01:05:43.206 --> 01:05:44.583
What if the chief walks through?

1202
01:05:44.607 --> 01:05:46.886
My bed says I take
my job seriously.

1203
01:05:46.910 --> 01:05:49.588
Your bed says your mama
didn't help you make it up.

1204
01:05:49.612 --> 01:05:51.690
Teaching another rookie
how to make his bed?

1205
01:05:51.714 --> 01:05:53.692
Somebody's got to.

1206
01:05:53.716 --> 01:05:55.895
That looks as bad as
yours did when I taught you.

1207
01:06:01.959 --> 01:06:05.238
<i>Engine 2, Engine 1,
Area 1, Battalion 1.</i>

1208
01:06:05.262 --> 01:06:07.873
<i>Respond to 209 11th Avenue.</i>

1209
01:06:07.897 --> 01:06:11.110
<i>Structure fire, residence.
Time out, 15:32.</i>

1210
01:06:11.134 --> 01:06:12.611
Michael, you got that? Got it.

1211
01:06:12.635 --> 01:06:14.613
Wayne, let's roll. Got it.

1212
01:06:27.384 --> 01:06:30.563
Engine 1 is en route to 209
11th Avenue, structure fire.

1213
01:06:30.587 --> 01:06:32.198
<i>10-4, Engine 1.</i>

1214
01:06:32.222 --> 01:06:34.000
Be advised we've
received numerous calls

1215
01:06:34.024 --> 01:06:36.502
<i>regarding this structure fire.</i>

1216
01:06:36.526 --> 01:06:38.771
All right. That means
there's something to this one.

1217
01:06:38.795 --> 01:06:41.155
Make sure you're tightened up.

1218
01:06:48.238 --> 01:06:50.816
Remember your training.
Stay with your partner.

1219
01:06:50.840 --> 01:06:52.285
Yes, sir.

1220
01:06:52.309 --> 01:06:53.719
Engine 1 is 10-23.

1221
01:06:53.743 --> 01:06:56.922
We have a single-story brick
dwelling, 30 percent involved.

1222
01:06:56.946 --> 01:06:59.058
We'll be using a 1"
and 3-quarter for rescue.

1223
01:06:59.082 --> 01:07:01.427
We'll be 11th Avenue Command.
Engine 2, bring me a line.

1224
01:07:01.451 --> 01:07:05.264
Be advised there is a
hydrant right next to Engine 1.

1225
01:07:05.288 --> 01:07:08.208
<i>Unit 2's clear. One supply line.</i>

1226
01:07:08.625 --> 01:07:10.669
Come on, rookie, let's go.

1227
01:07:10.693 --> 01:07:13.239
You live here? Is
everyone out of the house?

1228
01:07:13.263 --> 01:07:16.009
My daughter's in the neighbor's
house. This is our home.

1229
01:07:16.033 --> 01:07:18.677
Please, put that fire out.
We will, just stay clear.

1230
01:07:18.701 --> 01:07:20.813
Please, please. Oh, no. No!

1231
01:07:20.837 --> 01:07:23.116
Megan, Megan, where's Lacey?

1232
01:07:23.140 --> 01:07:24.750
She went home already.

1233
01:07:24.774 --> 01:07:26.386
What? She's not at your house?

1234
01:07:26.410 --> 01:07:28.787
No, I was just talking
to her on the phone.

1235
01:07:28.811 --> 01:07:30.645
Lacey!

1236
01:07:31.781 --> 01:07:33.426
- You can't go in there.
- Lacey!

1237
01:07:33.450 --> 01:07:36.329
You can't go in there. Let
me go. Please let me go.

1238
01:07:36.353 --> 01:07:38.431
My baby!

1239
01:07:38.455 --> 01:07:40.775
Let's go, let's go.
Come on, guys, let's go.

1240
01:07:42.759 --> 01:07:44.937
Lacey!

1241
01:07:46.663 --> 01:07:48.930
My baby. Oh!

1242
01:07:51.968 --> 01:07:53.812
Come on, guys. Come on, guys.

1243
01:07:55.038 --> 01:07:56.304
Let's go.

1244
01:07:58.175 --> 01:08:00.135
It's done. Charge.

1245
01:08:07.884 --> 01:08:10.129
Lacey!

1246
01:08:10.153 --> 01:08:11.433
Lacey!

1247
01:08:12.556 --> 01:08:13.955
Lacey!

1248
01:08:15.425 --> 01:08:17.358
Lacey!

1249
01:08:19.529 --> 01:08:21.262
Lacey!

1250
01:08:22.399 --> 01:08:24.043
Get in there,
guys, get in there.

1251
01:08:24.067 --> 01:08:25.587
Lacey.

1252
01:08:30.073 --> 01:08:33.252
Lacey! Lacey!

1253
01:08:33.276 --> 01:08:35.477
Come on. Over
here, man. Over here.

1254
01:08:45.655 --> 01:08:47.522
Back out, back out, back out.

1255
01:09:02.539 --> 01:09:04.272
Over here!

1256
01:09:05.375 --> 01:09:06.774
Over here!

1257
01:09:15.051 --> 01:09:16.395
There's a hydrant over there.

